  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "NPI Engineer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Keep track of and improve the yield of NPI parts by working with customers, product , process and quality engineers.</p></li><li><p>Develop new processes & new methods to improve plant’s capability in producing high end PCB.</p></li><li><p>Evaluate and qualify new materials to meet customers' requirement on electrical performance and thermal reliability of PCB.</p></li><li><p>To monitor and improve yield of NPI parts by working with Front End Engineering (FEE), Process Engineering, Manufacturing and Quality department.</p></li><li><p>Improve yield and lower cost of NPI parts by working with customer and supplier at design stage.</p></li><li><p>Ensure timely delivery of NPI parts by working with Production Control (PC) and Manufacturing on scheduling.</p></li><li><p>To lead failure analysis and ensure good closure of customer feedback on NPI quality issues.</p></li><li><p>Conduct and update FMEA and Control Plan of NPI parts.</p></li><li><p>Ensure smooth transfer of NPI parts to production.<br /></p></li></ul><p><strong>Job Requirements :</strong></p><ul><li><p>Minimum 2 years work experience in PCB related industry.</p></li><li><p>Minimum Degree or Diploma in Mechanical or Electrical Engineering.</p></li><li><p>Strong in Microsoft PowerPoint, Excel & Word.</p></li><li><p>Good communication skill.</p></li><li><p>Good in report writing.</p></li></ul>",
